 DSA Notes – Day 1 (Basics in Java)
 1. What is DSA?
 DSA = Data Structures + Algorithms
 Data Structure: Data ko store aur organize karne ka tarika.
 Algorithm: Problem ko solve karne ka step-by-step method.


 2. Variables
 Variables ek chhoti memory box jaisi hoti hain jisme data store hota hai. Har variable ka type hota
 hai:
 int age = 20;
 double price = 99.5;
 char grade = 'A';
 String name = "Amit";


 3. Loops
 Loops help karte hain ek hi kaam bar-bar repeat karne me.
 for(int i=1; i<=5; i++){
    System.out.println(i);
 }
 int j=1;
 while(j<=5){
    System.out.println(j);
    j++;
 }


 4. Functions (Methods)
 Function = ek chhota program ke andar program. Ek baar function banao → baar-baar use kar
 sakte ho.
 static int add(int a, int b){
    return a + b;
 }


 5. Taking Input (Scanner)
 Java me input lene ke liye Scanner class use hoti hai.
 import java.util.Scanner;
 Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
 int x = sc.nextInt();


 6. Summary
 1 Variables se data store karna aaya.
 2 Loops se repetition karna aaya.
 3 Functions se reusable code likhna seekha.
 4 Scanner se input lena aaya.

